caption: Nice place nice staff but the food is not worth the price and the portions are extremely small The miso soup was good though. I had the lobster crab rice and it was good but certainly not $29 worth.  The didn’t have a couple of the sakes that was on the menu also. Would not go back

If zero stars were an option that is exactly what I would give to this establishment. Had a reservation for 2 PM and was told there was a 15 minute grace period. I arrived to valet at 2:06 and was told we had to walk around the entire building which approximately took five minutes and put us at 2:11. Upon entering this establishment with the reservation I was told by the hostess Sophia there was a 10 minute grace period which was contradictory to what I was told previously. The manager Matt was little to no help. Very poor customer service and complete waste of time!! It’s unfortunate that my husband whom plays for the Ravens would recommend such a poor establishment.

Terrible! Had a reservation and it was not honored. Used their validation which is about a 5 minute walk, and received bad service from Sophia.  Maybe she was tired,  I don't know.  But the level of service I received was unacceptable
My daughter's 23rd birthday & we definitely enjoyed!!!!
Great food and ambient! Definitely try their cocktails.

Great food and a great experience. The restaurant is beautiful. The rolls are fairly expensive but are definitely worth it and are delicious. I had the flaming King crab roll and it was literally and figuratively on fire. 100% recommend for a good time.

The staff and the service is fantastic!!! The food is really delicious! All are must try! I love japanese cuisine and this place is just beyond amazing! Food is great plus the view of Baltimore harbor!!!!

I frequent Azumi a lot because of the romantic atmosphere but also because of the freshness of the food. The waygu fried rice is my personal favorite— so aromatic, melts right in your mouth; beautiful, savory blend of flavors! Quality ingredients and service. 5/5 would definitely recommend.
This spot simply knows how to treat their clients. Always with a welcoming attitude. The food is fairly priced, constantly fresh and clean.

Food and drinks were amazing! I loved the ambience of this sushi restaurant. Hostess was very accommodating  after my friends were late for their reservation. Waiter checked on us every chance she got to make sure things were taken care of I definitely will be back with my partner for date night !
I'm glad there is Azumi in Baltimore. The service is amazing and the fish is always fresh. Highly recommend the uni.

The food was wonderful. However, their ability to stick to COVID guidelines was horrendous. We arrived at 8:15 and the place seemed approximately at 50% capacity...not the 25% capacity Baltimore is allowed right now, but it wasn't so much a big deal to me. There were "Reserved for social distancing" signs at about every other table. By 9 pm, those signs were gone and every single table was filled with people. Not to mention a very loud table behind us which the wait staff stood with talking, masks down, and taking shots. For what we paid to eat there,  I am hoping I also did not pay to get exposed to COVID simply because this restaurant doesn't care about its guests.
Amazing experience. Mason is a great server.
The sushi was soo good and service was excellent!!!

My food tasted like floor cleaner it was so nasty I ordered the California tuna their fish is disgusting it’s like if you baked it in a car for three hours on the hottest day of the year please do not go here you will get sick

I love this place! They have first-cleass meals, their menu is decent, The chief cook in that place is a professional, I enjoy very much trying all their dishes. The food is always tasty, the attitude towards the clients  is helpful. I visit often this place and I not even once was unsatisfied. Highly recommended.
As with every Atlas group property excellence reigns supreme.

The ikura (salmon roe) was SOAKED is soy sauce in an attempt to mask the fact that it was clearly past it's prime.  I wouldn't have cared if I had been told they were out, but to try and deceive a customer is sketch-city.  Everything else from the service to the rest of the meal was excellent.  It's a shame I can't give them 5 stars, but I was left with a bad taste in my mouth both figuratively and literally.
Consistently 4 star food ruined by consistently 1 star service

The location is perfect for a Four Seasons guest, and the staff also has that legendary Four Seasons obsession with satisfying the customer.  The first good impression was finding Kirin Light on the menu: a very uncommon beer to find on a menu, and for those of us who like light beers, it is one of the best.  The sushi/sashimi selection is impressive (16 seafood types), also including an uncommon item: toro.  In fact, they have a Blue Fin Tuna "flight" of six pieces taken from three different areas of the belly, ranging from soft to butter.  You'll need to augment this with some appetizers, because it is both rich and on the petite side, but still worth it.  Like splurging for a finger of 18 year-old Macallan after dinner.
amazing sushi, awesome views and the ambience is on point
Japanese food, mmm, yummy. visited near twelve, it was not full. there was fast and courteous service.

japanese food and the setting here is quality. arrived at five, it wasn't busy. really nothing but great experiences here, so i will be back. it has a good interior. mood here is similar to fresno's scene.

Saturday lunch  It was a gorgeous sunny Fall day, with tables overlooking the water. Our Hispanic female server was very attentive, ebullient and courteous. The cocktails and sake selection was well curated and crafted well. FOOD:  We had the Wagyu fried rice, Emperors feast and Royal sushi selection and all the desserts. The sushi transported us back to the Tsukiji Tokyo market in freshness but the rice was not as well balanced. The crab roll was too overwhelmed with mayonnaise. The uni was VERY disappointing as it looked bright orange, dessicated and shriveled. She exuberantly quipped it was from Santa Barbara which excited us even more but in the end ...you could get better from your local Sushi place. Skip the small scoop of wagyu fried rice which was speckled on a greasy mound with a puddle of Siracha ..which totally overwhelmed the delicate beef taste...save the 21 bucks and order more sake! All the desserts were well balanced/unique and tasty....not to be missed.  Overall ...a pleasant dinning experience..in a more sanitized/mainstream Japanese meal ( nothing unique/authentic)  ,al fresco dinning  next to the water away from noisy traffic.

This is a great place to go for great food and nice atmosphere. I had the pleasure of having Johnathan, who was the bartender, he is absolutely phenomenal. He had a wealth of knowledge in both beverages and cuisine. His ability to describe the menu, allowed you to them make the best informed decision. Lots of great options to choose from. I will definitely be back.
My favorite place in Baltimore
Japanese food at this spot - yummy. The service was very helpful and observant.

Thank you azumi for a great time! Me and 7 of my sisters went to Baltimore and stayed at the hotel across the street. So we went 4 nights in a roll and every night  was a good time! Thanks zack, big budda,lol and Andrew for showing  your Detroit grls a goodtime azumi  style!!! So if you're in Baltimore make sure to check it out and tell the manager shawn I believe thats his name and zack his Detroit grls sent u!! Don't worry about the bouncer at the door telling u he has no seats. Tell him to step aside  you'll wait it's worth the wait!
Very pricey but yellowtail jalapeno just melts in your mouth. The miso cod is good too, but a bit salty.
Wonderful food and service ! I will be returning ♥️

This was our first time here and our visit was outstanding! Our server, Mason, was very attentive, personable, and knowledgeable of the items on the menu. The Flaming King Crab Roll was definitely my favorite - presentation and taste are a 10+! I started with the Rock Shrimp Tempura, which comes over a bed of baby lettuce and it was really tasty! The baby lettuce with the shrimp paired well!  My husband and I also had our 4 year-old daughter with us; however, be aware that the restaurant does not have a menu specifically for kids. With that, we ordered her a bowl of Vegetable Fried Rice but she did not like it (I did though - the red sauce around the plate was so good paired with the rice!). Our daughter let Mason know she did not like the vegetable fried rice and he brought her out a bowl of white rice (she didn't eat that either).  The vibe at Azumi is cute, grown, and sexy - lots and lots of candles and dim lights. There is seating outdoors, as well as inside - we sat inside. There are also plenty of heaters throughout the patio outside, too, so no need to worry about being cold in the fall and winter months. Next time my husband and I visit, we will definitely be kid-free and said we'd like to sit outside to enjoy to water views. 'Til next time Azumi!

Amazing restaurant! Beautiful ambiance by the water side especially if you are dining outside the view of the water is to die for!! Nice and friendly staffs and the food was worth everyone penny!! If you are in the Baltimore area this is one place to try!

Japanese food and the feeling here is quality. Great place to chill, get away, eat some good food. The staff was very helpful and observant. Prices were fair. Reminds me of a place in New York I liked to visit.
Always a great selection of fresh fish & fun dishes. Only 4 stars as they've become a bit persnickety with people who haven't made a reservation.

We ordered the Emperor's Sushi Feast to try at least once, and each piece was amazing - it almost melted in your mouth and the taste was light and fresh. Presentation for each dish was beautiful and their rice complimented the fish wonderfully. If you're drinking, I recommend the Natsuko and Harajuko.

For those in the area for the first time, consider this place for ambiance and a good view of the harbor if you can get the right seat. But do not expect much in terms of service or quality menu choices. We sat and it took 20 minutes for a hello from our waiter. All our apps and food was delivered before we received drinks. Wish we had gone to RA sushi up the street instead...

Best on the waterfront - service, view, outdoor dining, and great food. Authentic Japanese food including their A5 Wagyu steak (careful, it is sold by the ounce, minimum 4 oz @ $38/ounce). But, so well worth the experience!

Amazing tasting dinner there last night. My husband and I did the tasting menu and it was fabulous. The steak was probably the best I ever tasted, so tender and flavorful. Amazing!! They also have great cocktails, whiskeys, beers and the waiter was outstanding. They improvised a dink for me and it was sooo good. Highly recommend for a nice night out and great food. The ambience is also upbeat and fun. Dress up and go out to this place, you wont be disappointed!
Great sushi. Very expensive.

Super attentive bar tender, sushi was absolutely delicious, and host eat very kind to find us a spot open at the outdoor bar when all the tables outside were reserved. A great first time experience at azumi!
Worst ever. Manager was rude as hell.

Excellent birthday experience! Our server, Lena and the manager, Ian were so professional and nice to us! We got the best seat in the house (outside) and were recommended a bottle of Veuve to celebrate with. The menu items were great and artistically crafted. Yummy dessert to finish and a compliment glass of a new drink menu item which I will be coming back for. Awesome staff.
Love the place and always fresh fish😛

I went for a birthday celebration very nice place. The waiters was great and attentive. The food was great. Everything I ordered was great especially the vegetable fried rice and corn until I ordered the Lamb chop kimchi in which I was very disappointed. For the price I would have expected more. As you can see in the pictures this is all that came on the plate. Other restaurants I've visited has give more for the price. My food was placed on the table at 9:30p and I was told by the waiter at 9:45p she was going to bring me my check because we had to move outside at 10p. The drinks were very smooth great outdoor bartenders.
The atmosphere and food are wonderful

I was very worried about going out to eat as the cavileir attitude of the people does not give me any comfort. Azumi was busy but spaced out tables. Chef Alisher stopped by our table to check in on us and he was really very delightful.the Reisling we chose from the top of the list was excellent! I didn't take any photos of the Robata skewers, or my Miso black cod but the food was delightful!

My husband and I went to celebrate our anniversary. Atmosphere was very quiet and dimly lit. Food was tasty as well. Our waitress was somewhat attentive. While taking a sip of my drink I cut/knicked my lip on the rim of the glass. After alerting the waitress, they quickly corrected the problem. After about a half hour , my husband requested a drink.... this time he has a glass shard in his drink. (The rim of his glass was broken as well.) The waitress quickly apologized and the manager steered clear of us.  They “partially” comped our meal. I think that they should do a better job of the inspecting their glassware. I don’t believe we’ll be coming back.
Nice Location
It's not that great
Amazing atmosphere and wonderful food!! The wagyu fried rice is my favorite 🤤
LOVE Azumi's food and service!!!
Glad the outdoor seating is back open. Food and drinks were amazing.
I live for my nights at azumi, and their sushi 🍣 mmmmmm mmmm 😋

Excellent dinner tonight, 15 Feb. While its the day after, we celebrated Valentine’s Day date night here. Started with the rock shrimp tempura, then for dinner, had the prawn Robata, Maryland roll, salmon avocado roll, and a couple nigiri tuna/yellowtail toro. Food wear excellent. Very busy, and it was still good service. Nice drinks, Pinot noir, and a natsuko cocktail, and a little sake. Definitely a good restaurant to enjoy. It was our first time. We will come back!
Really loved happy hour in this place! Nice spot, will return anytime I'm in Baltimore
Let’s talk Sushi!

Located in the best spot of the Inner Harbour. This is a relatively new commercial area with lots of upper scaled buildings, restaurants, bars and hotels. People was running along the harbour bank during the sunset with fresh and relaxed air. The restaurant is a modern Japanese restaurant but will no Japanese in sight. The decorations are perhaps Japanese. The food was fantastic, well prepared and presented. The view was gorgeous. Our hosts were generous accompanied by good friends. A perfect evening. Very expensive $$$$ but if you can afford it, it is worth it.

Staff very nice , food delicious, very expensive, and music way way way way too loud. Everyone including waitresses are shouting to be heard. I asked to lower the extremely loud music and they said they couldn’t , bring ear plugs cause it’s unbearable. Anyone over 30 years of age just go for lunch, cause at 7:30 pm people don’t necessarily want to start shouting at each other over dinner, just crazy loud, both myself and date the next day had lost our voices. Waitress agreed that it’s out of hand.

Today I went to this sushi restaurant with my boyfriend. I do n’t know if that person is the manager. She did n’t let me go in with my boyfriend, because my boyfriend wore a pair of casual pants and she said that we could take out. I  I just feel that the environment is good and I want to eat in it, so I might as well cook at home, I am very disappointed, and we drove for an hour just to go there, and the parking fee also cost $ 5, I think the manager  Look down on us.

Amazing ambiance. A little loud but it is a buzzing atmosphere. The Flaming King Crab roll was amazing and not just because the plate was on fire. The Wagyu fried rice was also great! The Spicy beef tenderloin was also amazing. The food is a bit pricey, but well worth it. Our drinks were also exceptional.
Nothing special. Sooo expensive. Like 6 pieces of nigiri and one hand roll is $25. That's insane. Also zero cheap options.

Amazing as always. Every dish arrived at the table at just the right time! No stars taken away as I should have asked the server to clarify. I thought I ordered the A5 wagyu, instead I ordered the Australian wagyu. Either way it was delicious. A5 next time!

6 coworkers for a group dinner on a Monday night. Our server was very attentive. Our sushi orders were pretty quick, beautifully presented and delicious. Great sake selection. Cool atmosphere. Very dim lightning so no book reading here. 😉
Birthdays, parties, company dinners, dates....best place ever for any occasion. Try the lil tiny crabs.

A bit overrated - can get sushi that's just as good other places for much cheaper. And don't go at night unless you don't want to see the person sitting across from you (very dark - unless at the bar). Food was good though.
Sushi rice was mushy and had no flavor.
My husband took me out just because.  At first I said sushi again.  But trust me it was all simply amazing.  We found a new spot!!! Service was also impeccable.
The seats inside are very comfy

This Is the best sushi restaurant ever. It’s clean and fresh and all the food tastes outstanding. It was my friends birthday and they gave us ice cream for free. Their steak and sushi are both amazing and I really recommend going there.
If you want to waste your money and after that lay in bad with a stomach ache than this is your place! But the view is beutiful ...

I rarely write reviews but I felt like I needed to. This place is overrated and overpriced. Originally, I went years ago and spent $240 and remember feeling like I was duped. I was convinced to try it again so this was my second time going. The sushi is really just medicore. The seaweed salad was not good in my opinion. There were 5 different types of seaweed which I was excited about. But to my disappointment only 1 of the 5 was any good. Just give us classic seaweed salad. I also paid $24 for a rainbow roll that was below average and fell apart. The rice was soggy and the fish had a funky smell and was warm. However, I will say the service was pretty good and the food came out fast. Overall, In my opinion, you're better off going somewhere else. Save your dollars and just avoid the trendy hype.
Expensive, but food is solid. I’ll come solely to get the shrimp tempura appetizer.

We enjoy eating out. Yesterday we  found this fine place which friends told us about. We had a delightful experience there with first-rate dishes and a well-trained stuff and a great chief cook. We  added this restaurant in our phone list  and we will surely visit again soon. We deeply recommend.

This restaurant offers extraordinary service as well as delicious meals. My favourite restaurant in the city. The drinks and food served quickly and the prices were reasonable. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Girlfriend was sick, so I came in and asked for a bag. They gave me a bag. No idea how the food was, but the interior was lovely.
Great food, wonderful tastes, and unique dishes. A bit pricey, but you’re also paying for the location and view. Nice for special occasions, and very classy.
Really professional bartenders and excellent drinks. They really don't have any food options for vegans though, similar to the rest of Atlas group restaurants. 🙁
Honestly looking at all 4.5 star ratings we chose to come here.  Absolutely disappointing. Sushi wasn't fresh. Too expensive. Gets one star for location,  well mannered staff and cleanliness
terrible
Fuushi cocktail was awesome!!
Wow.  The best most delicate, delicious sushi I have had anywhere.  Excellent service and staff.  If you want a more quiet table ask for one in the back as the main room can be a bit loud.
Great service, amazing sushi & bento on waterfront
Best resturant in the City of Baltimore, the whole Azumi staff was wonderful with excellent service from the outside to the inside 😁⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Awesome food 👍😎🎉🎊

Very pricey for the amount of food you get.  Spent $300 for party of 3.  Also, forgot my credit card there and instead of shooting me a quick text or calling my cell (which they had bc I had made a reservation) to let me know so I could stop in to get it, they waited for me to figure out where I’d left it, which by that time, I had left the state to go home.  When I asked the manager why he didn’t contact me, he copped an attitude and said that he can’t track down every person that forgets their card.  Well, for a $300 dinner, I don’t think it was too much to ask to send me a text that would have taken literally 30 seconds. It’s called customer service!  Will not return.  Too many other great restaurants in that area to bother with a place that doesn’t appreciate my business.
Food is good, but now quite at  a 5 star, but probably the best in Baltimore.

This is usually one of my favorite places however we had reservations for 10(for a wedding anniversary) after the ravens game and we were told we could only have our drinks and then leave because we were in athletic wear, that's what people wear to football games, our table was even reserved for outside. I was very disappointed,  ruth chris had no problem seating us, BAD CALL AZUMI, FYI Ed Reed and his buddy were outside at the same bar as us with athletic wear on and no one asked them to leave
Great food - ordered Chirashi, Mushrooms and Sake. Very fresh fish, will definitely come back
Great scenery. Small portions.
Good place to hang out. IMHO appetizers need an overhaul. Sushi were pretty good, but nothing special.
Heather is wonderful, even gave me sunglasses!. The outside bar has an awesome view. And HH prices are great

I've had better Sushi for less money. It was not bad sushi just underwhelming. The fish was fresh. However the sushi roll fell apart. It was poorly made. The shrimp tempura roll lacked a certain crunch. Nigiri was small. Also the rice was not as sticky as it should be. The wagyu steak appetizer was delicious and the vegetable fried rice was one of the top fried rice dishes I have eaten. Maybe the steak options would be better.
Worth it!

For one reason or another, I had not eaten at this restaurant despite considering myself a sushi enthusiast.  Frankly, I am a regular at another great sushi restaurant in Columbia and I had thought that Azumi was just an overpriced and overrated sushi restaurant in the city.  The place I go to in Columbia treats me well and they get in some really nice stuff for the weekend.  With that said, I knew that I was in for a different experience at Azumi from the moment I laid eyes on the fresh fish at the sushi bar.  I was by myself which Is actually a great way to experience a great sushi bar because its easier to talk to the sushi chefs about what you like (seriously, try it).  I asked for a “tour” of the fish at the sushi bar and quickly developed a plan of attack.  I decided the Tuna tasting was a good base to build the rest of my meal upon.  I also ordered a live uni which I had only had once before and a couple of other orders of nigiri and a nice hand roll.  After this, I told the sushi chefs Mark and Billy what I liked and asked them to make a couple of things for me to finish my meal.  Everything I had was excellent.  The texture and temperature of everything I ate was about as perfect as it gets.  The service was great.  I can’t really even think of a criticism at the moment.  I don’t usually order many rolls when I get sushi, so I cannot comment much about them, but the rolls I saw going out to other customers looked really nice.  I plan to come back here to try the Omakase as soon as I can.  This is the best sushi restaurant in the Baltimore area, particularly if you consider yourself something of an advanced sushi eater.

I have never found a restaurant experience worth reviewing, but Azumi will be my first. After living in NYC and then LA, this has to be hands down the best all around Japanese sushi restaurant I have ever experienced. From the Yamazaki whiskey flight, sushi freshness, tuna sushi flight, fresh wasabi, beautiful deserts and service. All this on a Wednesday afternoon in downtown Baltimore - what an amazing surprise!

If you're looking for the highest end sushi in the city, you can end your quest! Compares to the best restaurants in downtown L.A. (Sugarfish, Shibumi, etc). I decided on the Azumi tasting platter and let the chef make his selections for the evening and I was unbelievably impressed with every course. The miyazaki wagyu was my favorite selection, as every succulent morsel simply dissolved in your mouth. I'm confident you could even eat it without teeth! For dessert, I reccomend the chocolate lava-cake, it takes up to 20 min or so to prepare, but you will be overwhelmed with bliss when the first spoonful reaches your lips. This was our first time here and we WILL return for another sample of their extensive, fresh, and unique menu. As an added bonus, go on a Friday or Saturday evening if you're a car enthusiast; it was an endless line-up of super cars rolling past our window booth (the Ferrari 488 was my favorite).
Took my boyfriend here for his birthday! Weve heard lots of good things and it was beyond what we thought. Service was amazing, the food was fresh and delicious. Definitely will be back!
Good fish and nice portion.
(Translated by Google) The best Japanese restaurant Baltimore.  (Original) Лучший японский ресторан Балтимора.
Bartenders give less than a shot.  Music is always good.
Ben is an amazing server, and highly recommend the tasting menu!
I didn't eat anything,  but the service was amazing.  The view of the harbor was great.
Great sushi. Great view. Heather is the best bartender!

Stellar location, excellent service, quality ingredients, poor execution. Sushi fell apart before I could get it off the plate. The nigiri rice crumbled beneath the fish and broke apart, the maki roll swung open like a door hinge. A few items on the menu were "trendy" but didn't live up to the hype, shishito peppers in particular. That I blame less on the restaurant and more on general trends. Flavor was excellent and ingredients were clearly quality. Maybe on a different day with different chefs it would have been worth what I paid, but not today. Service was stellar, especially considering how packed it was, and they comped our shishito order. It's not enough to entice me back, however.  PS This place has an excellent view of 4th of July fireworks.
This restaurant has an amazing atmosphere on the water! The sushi was rolled perfectly and not too sticky like the other places!
The best place in the area first time here an i was empress
This place has it all! Upscale Japanese food in a lovely waterfront atmosphere in Fells Point. The food was delicious and beautifully plated, and the service (at least for lunch) was good.
Graduation Party!

It is always a delight to dine at Azumi’s, but last night was especially wonderful as we were celebrating my special birthday!  Jenny, our server, is amazing and above and beyond.  Everything from food, service, and ambiance was perfection.  Thank you Azumi’s.
food was good . our waitress has issues....lkept trying to push the Tuna which I don't eat raw... ..then . "me: what kind of sides do you have? waitress in a D. Head tone: it's in the menu sir
The Japanese have been crafting sushi for centuries and the kind folks at Azumi do them justice with every roll.
Great Happy Hour specials.
Staff were friendly and attentive. Fresh sushi grade tuna. If you're a Sushi explorer you should go try Azumi. They have a dress code so make sure to check their website.
Food is ok but a bit pricey
Food was really fresh. Their whole fish was marvellous.

The food was amazing but be careful for the MKT price. The most expensive dish was a platter for about $250. Our waitress basically hustled us. We had a party of 6 and she casually recommended the 14oz Wagyu steak and didnt tell us that the price was around the same as the platter. To the managers of Azumi: Please advise your staff to explicitly inform customers of the MKT price. What the waitress did was dishonest and distasteful.
Really delicious food, drink menu was fantastic, our waiter, Benjamin, was awesome!

Very nice crowd and food... but it's a little pricey.  You pay for what you dont get. I would recommend taking someone you want to impress with nice but empty.  Order the drinks. One or two. Your bill will sure come to. 200
Very nice place and drinks.

Excellent! We stopped by after a concert at the MECU Pavillion and sat at the bar. Oren,our bartender,mixed great drinks right in front of us. I also ordered the salmon avocado sushi which was freshly cooked to order. The decor is beautiful and the restaurant had a great atmosphere! Nice outdoor bar and eating area that we'll have to try next time when the weather is warmer.

Service was great!!!
Food Mediocre

Parking was super easy to find , the garage was right next door and a short walk. The inside of this place is gorgeous and super clean. Our server was very MIA. Didn’t really say much or explain the menu and was gone for several minutes at a time. The food was delicious and the presentation was AMAZING. My sushi was literally on fire 😍😍. Definitely recommend 8/10. Great date night or birthday party.

Have been very hesitant to get here for various reasons, but finally pulled the trigger. Sadly, pretty much met expectations, while I truly was hoping for them to be exceeded. The service was above average, mostly attentive. Our server was very honest about choices we inquired about, which we were most appreciative of. The only reason for the two stars was the seafood pancake appetizer and the waguy (Australian) skewer. Both were delish. The fish was way overpriced for the quality. The tuna belly was fine, never find it to be worth the cost personally but the salmon and eel were actually tough to chew. Certainly strange experience and supremely disappointing. To top it off there was excessively loud club music, and bad club music taboot blasting in our ear. It’s was a pretty big miss.

Azumi refused to seat my sister because she was wearing ripped jeans, but as she was leaving noticed two other patrons seated and receiving service wearing ripped jeans.   She asked why they were able to be seated, but not her, they said it was up to the discretion of the manager.  I wonder why the manager allowed them, but not her...

The restaurant refused to seat me because I had ripped jeans on. Which is fine it is the policy, but as I walked away and looked in the window I saw two Caucasian people eating in the restaurant with ripped jeans. If a place is going to have a policy, it should be for everyone not for who they believe is acceptable to eat in the restaurant. I am a CPT in the Army and truly believe because I was African American with ripped jeans I was not “acceptable” to eat in there while the others could. When I mentioned the other individuals the manager said mine didn’t meant the inch requirement. Either way they will not get my service and will be talking to the owner about this manager. Policy is policy and should be enforced with everyone not on the selected few.

The Wagyu was awesome, kinda overpriced for the serving size but very good, service was lovely and professional, they even gave me a birthday card and ice cream which was much appreciated. I will be returning to try other delicacies!
Service was very slow for such expensive restaurant. Need to hire more servers.

Service was great as always. However, I used to come to Azumi all the time for the great service and the great fresh tuna. At my most recent visit the tuna was not fresh and a poor cut. I'm not sure if I'll be back.
The best Japanese in Baltimore. The sushi is the best by far. Expensive but worth it.
Beautiful atmosphere. Super thin slices of yellowtail on my roll so ... I think value is low. Prices too high for food but you pay for the view. Nice outdoor area.
Best sushi I have had anywhere... and I try sushi everywhere I go... worth the prices

Made a last minute reservation on Saturday night for 9:15. Food was nothing to write home about. Sashimi had no flavor and was watery. I guess the chef had not let it thaw out enough. Soup and salad were good but the roll my girlfriend ordered was covered with diced onions, so much that you couldn't taste any other aspect of the roll. The music was pretty loud and I guess we had problems communicating with our waitress since it took 2 separate ocassion's to flag her down and ask where are drinks were. Decor was nice and people were friendly. They sat us promptly at 915 and even gave us a choice of table. Might be willing to try something off the kitchen menu next time but definitely will not be ordering sushi/sashimi again. For the price of the dining experience I was hoping to compare it to my town home of NYC but clearly Baltimore is not even close to that level.

I took my boyfriend here for dinner on February 25th. The service was amazing; our server, Eric, was very knowledgeable about the sakes' particular flavor, especially when we were trying to choose between several descriptions that were similar, and how they would pair with the food that we chose. We do have dietary restrictions and he was very accommodating and honest about which items were easily made without dairy. His SA, Carolina, was super friendly and made us feel very invited (even though our dented honda wasn't good enough to be valeted with the Diamond white Benz's). She was perfectly attentive and quite familiar with the menu as well. This restaurant has a low-key, metropolitan, meet-me-after-dinner-with-the-girls-it'll-just-be-us atmosphere, lighting that really escalates the experience, and extremely welcoming staff; everyone who touched our table was a great personality! The only thing that was a disappointment was the booth which was too large to make the time we spent there very romantic. I saw the tables that were meant for two but they were much too crowded and did not have enough space to accommodate all the dishware needed for multiple courses or sushi. I would definitely go again!

Both times I’ve been here the service is stellar. Recently I came for my birthday and they even gave me a nice card. They also comped my dessert. I did get an Azumi Royal Platter and it was amazing! It’s for 2-3 people but between my girlfriend & I, we downed it easily. I took down about 70% on my own. I didn’t feel ridiculous afterwards either; still had room for dessert. It’s a beautiful restaurant, the lighting is moody so if you want photos, you’ll need some lighting. The nigiri and sashimi is the freshest you can find around.

The last time I went to Azumi, I had an amazing experience and wanted to tell everyone I knew. I finally dragged my boyfriend there and though parts of the meal were great, I wouldn't recommend it anymore.  Most of the food was amazing--the appetizers and entree we shared were fantastic. Bravo to the kitchen. The atmosphere and drinks were lovely as well. But the sushi was beyond bad.  One of the four rolls we got was great. The two specialty rolls were mediocre at best; not horrible, but not enjoyable and less flavorful than what we would typically get at a neighborhood sushi joint (much less an expensive one like this). One was the same roll I'd ordered a few months before; something had definitely changed because I thought it was fantastic that time. To call tonight's version lackluster in flavor would be a kindness.  The last roll, though: Ugh. It was a simple tuna roll. But the tuna was not good. It had a very off flavor--fishy in a BAD way-- and the texture was just wrong (suuuper mushy, like it was disintegrating).  The server took it off our bill which was nice, but nobody apologized or confirmed that we had been served spoiled sushi. When it's just a matter of personal preference, I would never get upset, but I've eaten enough raw seafood in my life to know something was seriously wrong. Unfortunately, I won't be back.

Great food, cool hip atmosphere, and excellent service. Definitely on the higher-priced side, but worth it with the level of service and quality you get.

But honestly they were all soo good!  Also chef Andy gave us some really delicious eggplant and there was this amazing seared live scallop dish that was soo fresh and tasty. Eric was our server, and he was super attentive and helpful, too! I can't wait to come back :)

Top notch food and beverage environment! I chose this place... Well I didn't choose this place, my good good girlfriend chose this place for me to have my birthday happy hour, and I'm so thankful that she did! This place has everything, when I say everything... I mean everything! The ambience was fantastic! The inside of the establishment is beautiful as well as beautifully decorated w a Japanese theme to it; mixed with a little of American. There is plenty of outdoor seating, I mean PLENTY... almost as much seating as indoor! Beautiful views of the Baltimore Inner Harbor from every seat outdoor and indoor! The bar is beautiful, well-lit, well-stocked, and has the best bartenders ever! Fantastic drink recommendations, as well as you get a show each time they make a drink! I am so happy with the decision made to visit this establishment that I can't stop saying it! We ordered plenty of drinks... food items... Everything our little heart desired & everything ordered was delivered to our seats quickly! I even tried new menu items I've never tasted before, and they came out wonderful! I definitely look forward to returning back here in the near future to try some other items as well as get some other specialty cocktails from the wonderful bartenders!  The only issue I have with this place, valet parking is $12! I thought that was pretty expensive for the area that the restaurant was in, but worth it if you're in a rush... And I was in a rush! I must admit, even the valet guys were very very nice! They had a great sense of humor and they handled my car with care, so maybe it wasn't so bad, and maybe I will valet again just so I can interact with them. This restaurant location is not far from the other shops here at Harbor East, therefore you can park elsewhere and just walk over. There's also a garage connected to the same building as well as across the street that shares with the hotel if you want other parking options.
Beautiful! Exceptional Staff, Delicious food at reasonable prices! Can't wait to go back for another happy hour

very good sushi. it seems like they lowered the sushi price just little bit, along with the size. The service is mediocre. The quality/ freshness seem to vary, which is not good...

Visited Azumi this Saturday for a birthday party! Was not happy with the service, but was not going to complain. Sunday I was severely sick with food poisoning and felt extremely bad. In the morning today I found out that 4 other people from the birthday party had the same symptoms, and one girl nearly got to the hospital after fainting! I'm extremely upset! I found out that people were poisoned there before multiple times! How is this possible in 5* place??? This is absolutely outrageous! I'm going to file a complaint to Baltimore City board of health. If it won't shut them down then at least more inspections will be performed and other customers will not suffer like we did! I'm still recovering. The worst I have ever felt in my life! I will not let it slide!

I love good sashimi and this place has some of the best I have ever had.  However, we are unlikely to return.  Parking is abysmal. I didn't expect free parking but damn, the closest parking garages are mostly reserved or valet.     It really puts a damper on a date when you spend 30+ minutes getting parking. When we got to the restaurant we were the second table seated...and somehow forgotten about.  It took 30 minutes to get a drink order, another 20 after that for our food order, and just under an additional hour to get sashimi. SASHIMI. We tempted desert and the wait was just as long as everything else. We saw people around us seated, served, and out the door who had arrived long after us.  We were there for three hours.  While the food was stellar, it put my husband and I off on our weekly date night. We won't be returning.  If you have a ton of time and are staying locally, the food is top notch...but the service...failed.

Both times I've been to Azumi, the staff was knowledgeable and friendly, the food and drinks were wonderful, and the atmosphere was inviting. Despite the dress code warning on the door, we have definitely been in jeans and a nice shirt. Will definitely go again.

If I could write "WOW" 100 times in a row I'd do it. This is amazing! What a phenomenal place. As usual, great location but the sushi is outstanding. Literally the best I've ever had!

Upscale Japanese fusion restaurant with great harbor views and expensive prices. Fancy interior and club music playing in the background throughout. The sushi was excellent, but extremely expensive for just a cut of fish. Entrees and appetizers were good, but nothing groundbreaking. Again, for that price level you kind of expect more. One thing that did stand out were the signature mixed drinks which were excellently crafted and presented. After trying a couple selections, each cocktail had a very deep palate that is hard to find anywhere else. Overall, Azumi makes for a great night out for a special occasion or if you have money to burn. However, just be aware that you are paying for the privilege.

the staff are super friendly and it closes late which is always a plus

By chance discovered they have an attractive happy hour menu. Dishes were decently sized and ranged between $5-8. Sapporo and Kirin Light regular sized drafts were only $2! Three of us decided to make it into an early dinner, ordered practically one of everything, and left very content and sated. This rating is strictly for happy hour, but one in our party had been there before for dinner and felt the quality of the dishes was the same. Note that happy hour is only available inside and not in the patio area, based on what our server explained.

We went for the Chef's Tasting Menu and, despite it being 5 courses, we were told the courses would be smaller portions of many of their dishes so we were assuming we'd maybe get 5 bite sized dishes - we were so wrong, and SO stuffed. The entire meal was amazing, and well worth it.  The drinks were very well made - we went for almost one of every cocktail throughout the night and every single one was awesome.  If you're not going for the tasting menu, I definitely recommend at least going for the king crab legs hot appetizer - the spicy soy butter on top of very meaty claws/legs was amazing.  We'll be back for sure.

Terrible prices for what you are actually getting. Fancy prices make you think the food will be fancy too. $7 regular Japanese house salads?? Seriously? I ordered the spicy tuna roll ($10) and got poop on a plate. It was ok tasting but their spicy sauce was mostly mayo and the tuna inside was a big lump that was weirdly firm. When I asked if they could ask crunch flake to the roll, they responded with no. Yet my husbands roll came with it on it? No special orders I guess? Idk. And when the server asked how was everything, and I stated my distaste, he just "I'm sorry" and left. ???? Ok weirdo! Why ask if you aren't going to fix it. Don't think I'll be back.

After Pabu's departure from the Harbor East Four Seasons, I was worried Baltimore wouldn't be able to experience high-end Japanese cuisine any longer. That fear is irrelevant now with Azumi's arrival in the city. The food, cocktails, and service have been 5 stars. Can't wait to see how this place continues to grow and change the Baltimore dining scene!
